  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building equitable resilience to climate change and disasters in Ben Tre</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is under PIP P00629 will be implemented in two of the coastal districts of Ben Tre Province prone to sea level rise impacting on agriculture, shrimp farming, forestation, water and other livelihoods. Through this project, the resilience of poor people (in particular women) in coastal communities in four communes of Binh Dai and Thanh Phu districts of Ben Tre province, will be significantly increased  through reducing vulnerability to impacts of disasters and climate change. This version reflected funding source through OGB  and NZAID.Total fund for this project in 2011 and 12 is GBP 107,430.</narrative>
  </description>
